summary:
Here is a clear and concise summary of the Security Council document:

The Security Council:

Recalling previous resolutions and statements on the Great Lakes region, particularly resolutions 1649 and 1650, and resolutions on strengthening the effectiveness of the Security Council and cooperation between the UN and regional organizations;

Reaffirming respect for sovereignty, territorial integrity, and political independence of States in the region;

Condemning the 1994 genocide in Rwanda and armed conflicts in the Great Lakes region, and expressing concern at human rights and humanitarian law violations;

Aware of the link between exploitation of natural resources, illicit trade, and proliferation of arms fuelling conflicts;

Expressing concern at the devastating impact of conflict on the humanitarian situation;

Welcoming efforts by the Tripartite Plus Joint Commission and the International Conference on Peace, Security and Stability;

Recognizing progress in peace processes, particularly in Burundi and the Democratic Republic of the Congo;

 Commends the Secretary-General, African Union, and other stakeholders for organizing the First Summit of the International Conference;

 Urges countries to continue collective efforts to promote good relations, peaceful coexistence, and resolution of disputes;

 Calls upon countries to agree on confidence-building measures based on concrete actions;

 Encourages finalizing preparations for the second Summit in Nairobi, focusing on peace and security issues, to adopt a Security, Stability and Development Pact.
